SIMPLE: overpass
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overpass
<hw>O`ver*pass"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overpassed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overpassing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Surpass</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To go over or beyond; to cross; <as>as, to
<ex>overpass</ex> a river; to <ex>overpass</ex> limits.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To pass above; -- of roadways and other paths;
<as>as, the highway <ex>overpasses</ex> the railroad
tracks</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To pass over; to omit; to overlook; to
disregard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the beauties of the East⟦br⟧
He slightly viewed and slightly <qex>overpassed</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To surpass; to excel.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>R. Browning.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overpass</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overpass
<hw>O`ver*pass"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To pass over, away, or
off.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>overpass</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: overpass
<hw>o"ver*pass`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A road or other
pathway which passes over another road, railroad, or other path; <as>as,
he stopped on the street under the railroad
<ex>overpass</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overpassionate</ent>⟦br⟧
